series_description:
Project records related to planning, design,
construction, conversion, or modernization
of state facilities, structures, infrastructure,
and systems, including feasibility,
screening, and implementation studies;
topographical and soil surveys and reports;
as-builts; laboratory test reports;
environmental impact statements;
correspondence; successful and
unsuccessful bid documentation and other
related documentation.

Physical documents may include: Email;
letters/correspondence; notices;
settlement agreements; exclusion data
base materials; MPI investigative
materials; closure memo; final report;
Attorney work product: memos, notes,
etc.; materials from THMP/MCOs/DMOs
regarding Provider Enrollment; MCO/DMO
SIU referral materials; Accurint Reports;
pleadings; discovery; expert materials;
CD/DVD/Thumb Drives with data; patient
file materials.

